original: Busck, Erik Gustaf, jägmästare, Borås, f. 2/9/85 i Jönköp. av handl. Gustaf B. o. Hilda Malmberg. G. 23 m. Mimmy Palm. — Stud:ex. 04, ex. v. skogsinst. 11. E. jägmäst. 12, assist, o. e. jägmäst. inom Smål. distr., Kop-parb. revir o. Hallens revir 12-26, ord. jägmäst. i Görjeå revir 26-33, jägmäst. i Jörns revir 33-38, i Ahngsås revir sed. 39. RVO.
translated: Busck, Erik Gustaf, forest supervisor, Borås, b. September 2, 1885, in Jönköping, son of merchant Gustaf B. and Hilda Malmberg. Married in 1923 to Mimmy Palm. He passed the school leaving exam in 1904, and forest inspector exam in 1911. Became a forest supervisor in 1912, an assistant and deputy forest supervisor in the Småland district, Koppars and Hallen's district from 1912-1926. He became a regular forest supervisor in Görjeå's district from 1926-1933, a forest supervisor in Jörn's district from 1933-1938, and in Ahngsås district since 1939. He was awarded the Royal Order of Vasa.
